 Eight suspects have been arrested for the brutal murder of two
people. The incident happened at GaMolepo in the Mankweng in Limpopo. Thabane Mokgohloa (58) and Mack Mashapa (55) were on Monday
hunted down, kidnapped from their homes and brutally killed after they were
accused of stock theft. Police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said their
charred bodies were found in the bushes at Dihlopaneng, GaMolepo. The suspects were arrested during a crime intelligence driven
operation that was conducted Koppermyn and Mmatobole villages in GaMaja area as
well as Laastehoop in gaMolepo. The operation was comprised of members from Crime Intelligence,
Mankweng detectives and the Tracking Team. A vehicle believed to be the one used to transport the suspects
was confiscated. The Provincial Commissioner of the South African Police Service
in Limpopo, Lieutenant General Nneke Ledwaba has commended the members for
swiftly arresting these suspects a day after the gruesome discovery of the
deceasedâ€™s bodies. The suspect will face charges of two counts of murder,
kidnapping and malicious damage to property. They are expected to appear in
Mankweng magistrate court soon. 